[Minnesota has been trying to eliminate this disease from the state for
several years. The elimination process proceeds. Tuberculosis is caused by
the bacterium _Mycobacterium bovis_. Although this bacterium primarily
affects bovines, it can affect a wide range of mammals, including humans,
swine, and deer. - Mod.TG

The state of Minnesota can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail
interactive map at <http://healthmap.org/promed?v=40,-97.6,4>. - CopyEd.MJ]
